The Newspaper Vendors Association, Abuja (NVAA) has joined other Nigerians in celebrating the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila, at 56. The message was contained in a letter made available to Daily Trust jointly signed by the Chairman and Secretary of NVAA, Comrade Idris Nababa Hassan and Ikoi Philips respectively. The message reads in part: “On behalf of NVAA, the stakeholders, BoTs and our patrons, we wish to join millions of Nigerians in rejoicing with our leader, brother, associate and father, Hon Femi Gbajabiamila, the Speaker of the House of Representatives, on your 59th birthday celebration. “Your humility and leadership qualities, as well as your patriotism in handling the affairs of the 9th House of Representatives, have led to the success so far recorded. May Allah bless you with more wisdom, mostly at this trying moment.”